      خُبَعْثِنٌ: see خُبَعْثِنَةٌ. ― 
       -b2-  Also Plump in body;
or fat, soft, thin-skinned, and plump, in body;
applied to any thing [i. e. to any animal]. (K.)


      4 
      اخبى, inf. n. إِخْبَآءٌ; (Ks, TA;) or اخبى خِبَآءٌ;
(S, K;) and ↓ تخبّى, (Ks, TA,) or تخبّى خِبَآءً;
(S, K;) and خِبَآءً ↓ خبّى, (S, * K,) inf. n. تَخْبِيَةٌ;
(S;) He made a [tent such as is called] خبآء:
(Ks, S, K:) and he set it up. (K.) [see also
10.] And أَخْبَيْتُ كِسَائِى I made my [garment
called] كسآء to be [as] a خِبَآء. (TA.)


      خُرٌّ and ↓ خُرِّىٌّ The لُهْوَة of a mill or mill-stone;
i. e. the place into which the wheat is thrown
with the hand; (S;) the mouth of a mill or millstone. (K.)


      خُزُمٌ [a pl. of which the sing is not mentioned]
Sewers of skins or hides or boots and the like;
syn. خَرَّازُونَ. (TA.)


      خُسْرٌ an inf. n. of خَسِرَ. (S, Msb, K.) In the
Kur ciii. 2, accord. to some, it means Punishment
for sin. (TA.)


      خَصِيلٌ: see خَصِيلَةٌ, in two places.  
    -A2-  Also
Overcome [in a shooting-match, or] in a contest
for stakes or wagers. (JK, K.)  
    -A3-  And A tail;
(K, TA;) as, for instance, of a [wild] bull. (TA.)


      خَضِدٌ (assumed tropical:)  Lacking power to rise, (K, TA,) from
languor of the body, and pain, with laziness;
(TA;) as also ↓ مَخْضُودٌ. (K.)


      أَخْطَبَانُ a [proper] name of A certain bird;
(K, TA;) so called because of a خُطْبَة, i. e.
خُضْرَة, in its wings. (TA.)


      خَمُوشٌ Gnats: (S, A, K:) in the dial. of
Hudheyl: (S:) n. un. with ة: or it has no n. un.;
(TA;) one thereof being called بَقَّةٌ. (S.)


      خُورٌ a pl. of خَوَّارَةٌ, (S, K,) contr. to rule;
(MF, TA;) and of خَوّار in the phrase خَوّارُ العِنَانِ.
(JK, TA.) See خَوَّارٌ, in five places.
